MULTI-LAYER CAPITAL ALLOCATION SYSTEM v3.1
==========================================
Institutional-grade, regime-aware framework for Nifty 50 stock allocation.
Last updated: 2026-04-27 — reflects implemented constants in constants.py.

---

OBJECTIVE
---------
A regime-based, multi-factor framework to decide:
  1. WHEN to invest  (timing)
  2. WHAT to invest in  (selection)
  3. HOW MUCH to invest  (position sizing)

Universe: Nifty 50 stocks (NSE). Review cadence: monthly.

---

PART 1 — THE 9 FACTORS
-----------------------
The weighted composite score is built from 9 factors across 3 layers.
All factor scores are pre-normalised to [−1, +1] before weighting.

  MACRO LAYER
  ┌─────────────────┬────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Factor          │ Weight │ Data source / interpretation                  │
  ├─────────────────┼────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ liquidity       │  0.25  │ RBI Liquidity_Indicator. Positive = loose.    │
  │ rates           │  0.15  │ RBI Repo_Rate. Lower rate = positive signal.  │
  │ credit_growth   │  0.10  │ RBI Credit_Growth YoY. High = early cycle.    │
  └─────────────────┴────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  EQUITY LAYER
  ┌─────────────────┬────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ valuation       │  0.15  │ Screener PE + PB. Low = cheap = positive.     │
  │ earnings        │  0.10  │ Screener EPS + ROE. High = positive.          │
  │ relative_strength│ 0.10  │ Stock 6M return / Nifty 6M return. >1 = good.│
  └─────────────────┴────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CROSS-ASSET LAYER  ⚠ data gap — fed as 0.0 (neutral) until wired
  ┌─────────────────┬────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ usd_lens        │  0.05  │ Nifty / USD ratio. Global capital flow proxy. │
  │ gold_lens       │  0.05  │ Nifty / Gold ratio. Inflation-adjusted lens.  │
  │ sector_strength │  0.05  │ Sector index vs Nifty 50. Rotation signal.   │
  └─────────────────┴────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Total weight: 1.00  ✓

Composite score formula:
  score = Σ (factor_score × factor_weight)
  Clamped to [−1, +1]. Rounded to 4 decimal places.

