PART 2 — SIGNAL COMPUTATIONS
------------------------------

  ROC (3-month momentum)
    ROC = (price_now − price_3m_ago) / price_3m_ago
    Source: Kite Connect daily closing prices (90-day window).

  Asymmetry Index
    Asymmetry = (−valuation_score) + earnings_score + liquidity_score
    Measures risk/reward skew. Positive = more reward than risk.

  Relative Strength
    RS = stock_6m_return / nifty_6m_return
    Guard: if Nifty return = 0, RS = 1.0 (neutral fallback).
    Source: Kite Connect 180-day closing prices.

  Time Stop
    Count consecutive months (from most recent) with no meaningful price
    movement. "Meaningful" = monthly change ≥ 5%.
    Rule: ≥ 12–18 months without movement → consider exit.
    Source: monthly closing prices, oldest first.

---

PART 3 — DECISION MATRIX
--------------------------
Three signals are bucketed, then looked up in a 27-entry matrix.

  Score buckets:
    high   → composite_score > 0.5
    mid    → −0.5 ≤ composite_score ≤ 0.5
    low    → composite_score < −0.5

  Momentum buckets (ROC):
    up     → ROC > 0.05
    flat   → −0.05 ≤ ROC ≤ 0.05
    down   → ROC < −0.05

  Asymmetry buckets:
    pos     → asymmetry_index > 0.3
    neutral → −0.3 ≤ asymmetry_index ≤ 0.3
    neg     → asymmetry_index < −0.3

  Full matrix (score, momentum, asymmetry → signal):

    HIGH score:
      (high, up,   pos)     → strong_buy
      (high, up,   neutral) → buy
      (high, up,   neg)     → buy
      (high, flat, pos)     → buy
      (high, flat, neutral) → hold
      (high, flat, neg)     → hold
      (high, down, pos)     → hold
      (high, down, neutral) → sell
      (high, down, neg)     → sell

    MID score:
      (mid, up,   pos)     → buy
      (mid, up,   neutral) → buy
      (mid, up,   neg)     → hold
      (mid, flat, pos)     → hold
      (mid, flat, neutral) → hold
      (mid, flat, neg)     → hold
      (mid, down, pos)     → hold
      (mid, down, neutral) → sell
      (mid, down, neg)     → sell

    LOW score:
      (low, up,   pos)     → sell
      (low, up,   neutral) → sell
      (low, up,   neg)     → strong_sell
      (low, flat, pos)     → sell
      (low, flat, neutral) → strong_sell
      (low, flat, neg)     → strong_sell
      (low, down, pos)     → sell
      (low, down, neutral) → strong_sell
      (low, down, neg)     → strong_sell

  5 output signals:
    strong_buy   🚀  All three dimensions aligned bullish
    buy          🟡  Score + at least one more dimension positive
    hold         ⚪  Mixed or flat signals
    sell         🔴  Score deteriorating or negative momentum
    strong_sell  ⚫  Score < −0.5, regime clearly negative

