PART 4 — POSITION SIZING
--------------------------
Final Size = Base Allocation × Conviction Multiplier × Volatility Adjustment

  Layer 1 — Base allocation (by signal):
    strong_buy   →  85%
    buy          →  65%   (confirmed: PRD example Score +0.61 = 65% base)
    hold         →  30%
    sell         →  15%
    strong_sell  →   5%

  Layer 2 — Conviction multiplier (by composite score):
    score ≥ 0.5              →  1.5×  (strong alignment)
    0.0 ≤ score < 0.5        →  1.0×  (moderate)
    score < 0.0              →  0.5×  (weak)

  Layer 3 — Volatility adjustment (by stock beta vs Nifty):
    beta < 0.8               →  1.1×  (low vol — size up slightly)
    0.8 ≤ beta < 1.2         →  1.0×  (market-like — no adjustment)
    beta ≥ 1.2               →  0.8×  (high vol — size down)

  Example (from PRD):
    Signal = Early Accumulate (buy), Score = +0.61, Beta ≈ 1.0
    Base = 65% × Conviction = 1.5× × Vol = 1.0× = 97.5% of base allocation

  Hard risk controls (not computed, applied by investor):
    - Max single stock: 10–15% of total portfolio
    - Min cash reserve: 10–20%
    - Drawdown rule: 15–20% drawdown → reduce position

